absolute
children.definition: Return a time series that contains the absolute value of each data point.

children.label: average
children.definition: Return a time series with the average value of the data points over the selected plotting range.

children.label: beta
children.definition:
Returns beta of two time series in a given window of n periods.

Beta(x, y) = Covariance(x,y) / Variance(y)

beta is a measure of x's volatility in relation to y. It indicates how well x's movement correlates to y's movement.

children.label: correlation
children.definition: Return the linear correlation of two time series in a given window of n periods.

children.label: change
children.definition: Calculate the one-period change for a series, same as delta(expr).

children.label: change percent
children.definition: Calculate the cumulative normal distribution for a series.

children.label: cumulative
children.definition: Calculate the one-period percentage changefor a series - Same as delta_pct(expr).

children.label: cumulative series
children.definition: Return a time series with the sum of the data point from the beginning of the plotting range to the date in the time series.

children.label: delta
children.definition: Calculate the one-period change for a series, same as chg(expr).

children.label: delta percent
children.definition: Calculate the one-period percentage changefor a series, same as chg_pct(expr).

children.label: exponential
children.definition: Calculate exponential for each data point in the time series and return the new time series.

children.label: exponential moving average
children.definition: Return exponential moving average in a given window of n periods.

children.label: historical logarithmic volatility
children.definition: Return the historical logarithmic volatility in a given window of n periods.

children.label: historical standard deviation
children.definition: Return the standard deviation in a given window of n periods.

children.label: historical volatility
children.definition: Return the historical volatility in a given window of nn periods.

children.label: natural log
children.definition: Calculate natural log for each data point in the time series and return the new time series.

children.label: moving average
children.definition: Return moving average in a given window of n periods.

children.label: mzscore
children.definition: Return the outlier of a moving average in a given window of n periods.

children.label: period high
children.definition: Return the maximum in a given window of n periods.

children.label: period low
children.definition: Return the minimum in a given window n periods.

children.label: rate change percent
children.definition: Calculates the rate change percentage of a series against the first point in the series. If a date (optional) is passed to the function, the rate change percentage is based on the value of the specified date.

children.label: round
children.definition: Round the given time series value to the nearest n decimals.

children.label: rolling regression
children.definition:
A rolling regression is where the parameters are estimated on a moving data window rather than on the full data set.

EST estimate of the value lookAhead periods ahead of the last point int the regression.

RES residual of the value lookAhead periods ahead of the last point int the regression.

C0..CN coefficient of dependend variable N - CN (last coefficient) gives the intercept.

RSQ R-squared value of the regression.

SEE standard error of the estimate.

ZSC zscore of the last residual in the rolling window.

FST F-statistics provides a measure for the probability that different sets of data have the same variance.

SGF Significance of F-statistics, with a value between between 0 and 1.
children.syntax: regress(token, ind. var 1-N, dep var, points)

children.label: rsi
children.definition: A measure of the sum of ups and the sum of downs in a given window of n periods, normalized to be a number between 0 and 100. The higher the result, the more frequently the expression has been going up in that window.

children.label: smooth rsi
children.definition: A smooth measure of the sum of ups and the sum of downs in a given window of n periods, normalized to be a number between 0 and 100: the higher the result, the more frequently the expression has been going up in that window.

children.label: square root
children.definition: Calculate square root for each data point in the time series and return the new time series.

children.label: standard deviation
children.definition: Return a time series with the standard deviation of the data points over the selected plotting range as entire population. Equivalent to Excel's stdevp() function.

children.label: standard deviation for sample
children.definition: Return a time series with the standard deviation of the data points over the selected plotting range as a sample. Equivalent to Excel stdev() function.

children.label: truncate
children.definition: Truncate the given time series value in n decimals.

children.label: zscore
children.definition: Return a time series outlier with the average value of the data points over the selected plotting range.

children.label: begin of month
children.definition: Return the first data point of each month.

children.label: begin of quarter
children.definition: Return the first data point for the beginning of each quarter.

children.label: begin of year
children.definition: Return the first data point for the beginning of year.
